ol.li: Primary Consume: The / character is always consumed first by advance().

LA(1) Priority:
_match('/') is checked first. If true, the second / is consumed.
_match('*') is checked only if the first check fails.
Fallthrough: If neither sequence matches, the scanner emits a single-character OPERATOR token.
State Reset: Comments return None, causing the main scan_tokens() loop to ignore the lexeme and restart in NORMAL mode.
